body:
It seems better to avoid lying about the capabilities of the type and only expose the straight efficient path through `sq_item()`. That allows calling (i.e. subscripting) code to take appropriate decisions itself.

Closes https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/5729
Based on https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/7434
See comment in https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/7434#issuecomment-3694571349

commit.message:
Improve benchmarks scaling for sub-benchmarks by scaling to the fastest benchmark instead of the slowest.
Scale back the timings of sub-benchmarks to the outer scale count to report comparable timings.

Implement sequence and mapping protocols depending on user signature.
Implement both as before, but prefer sq_item() over mp_subscript() if the index argument of the user implemented "__getitem__" method is a C integer.
Do the same split for setitem/delitem.

Closes https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/5729
Fix function cast.
Do not implement the mapping slots if the key/index argument type of the slot method is a C integer.
Update documentation.
Move decision about subscript slot implementation entirely into TypeSlots.py.
Fix comments.
Call known base type methods directly, if available.
Always implement the Mapping protocol if inheritance is involved.
Add a generated test for all combinations of special subscript methods and inheritance.
Rename variable.
Fix f-string syntax in older Python versions.

Give users complete control over the sequence/mapping collection type by implementing missing alternatives.
Extend the tests to include missing cases.

Turns out, we cannot just avoid implementing the mapping protocol for @collection_type("sequence").
That would prevent extended slicing.
We can only do it if the methods have a Sequence signature.
Merge branch 'master' into getitem_split
Extend test to include the @collection_type() variations.
Improve comment.
Further reduce code overhead in test.
Add a micro benchmark for subscripting.
Benchmarks: Allow debug output from benchmark modules via stderr.
Benchmarks: Reduce maximum variance of timings to a more reasonable value.
Add NumPy arrays to getitem benchmark collections.
Benchmarks: Terminate each sub-benchmark after at most 60 seconds.
Extend benchmark.
Remove unfair overhead from benchmark.
Extend benchmark to make actual use of @collection_type(), if supported, and also time the subscripting from Python.
Shorten benchmark names.
Merge branch 'getitem_bench' into getitem_split
Typo.
Merge branch 'getitem_bench' into getitem_split
Reduce benchmark runtimes by skipping the initial external warmup run.
Speed up benchmark autoranging.
Exclude slow benchmark outlier runs (> +15%).
Speed up benchmark autoranging by avoiding the final step adaptation.
Merge branch 'getitem_bench' into getitem_split

Log benchmark results right after finishing a single benchmark module run.
This gives quicker insights long before the complete results are printed at the end of the run.
Prevent scale <= 0 as result of autoscaling.
Merge branch 'getitem_bench' into getitem_split
Stop autoscaling when the change goes against 0.
Merge branch 'getitem_bench' into getitem_split
